HEADWORD: Falciform
<hw>Fal"ci*form</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>falx</ets>, <ets>falcis</ets>, a sickle + <ets>-form</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>falciforme</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having the shape of a scithe or
sickle; resembling a reaping hook; <as>as, the <ex>falciform</ex>
ligatment of the liver</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

